cs.CR, cs.NI, cs.LG, cs.SE, cs.DC 

The paper focuses on enhancing the security of mobile collaborative learning (MCL) by detecting and blocking malicious attacks, specifically rogue DHCP servers. This topic falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR) and network security (cs.NI). The paper also introduces a new algorithm and mathematical model, which could fall under machine learning (cs.LG) and software engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the paper validates the idea through simulation, which could fall under distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC).
